    <p class="section-number">06, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Monogram jobs from across the territory.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Three representative service calls — model, symptom, diagnosis, repair, and cost. Names and addresses omitted; technical scenarios are typical of what we see on Monogram service.</p>

    <div class="repair-grid">
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Monogram ZISS420DNSS 42" built-in side-by-side, Beverly Hills</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Ice production dropped to nothing over a 3-week window. Water dispenser slowed to a trickle at the same time. Owner noticed mineral residue building up in the dispenser tray. Unit was 7 years old, in the 2018 production cohort.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2015-2020 ZISS ice maker fill valve failure pattern, accelerated by Beverly Hills LADWP hard-water supply. Valve orifice heavily mineral-restricted. Ice maker assembly itself tested clean — fill valve was the isolated failure but ice maker had been running under restricted flow for several months and showed early wear.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Fill valve replacement with OEM Monogram part (in stock on truck for ZISS series). Flushed water line and dispenser tray. Recommended 4-year preventive valve service interval given the address's hard-water profile. Verified normal ice production and dispenser flow over 24 hours.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $245 total. Same-day, completed on diagnostic visit in 75 minutes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Monogram ZIC360NNRH 36" integrated column refrigerator, Hancock Park</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Owner reported fresh-food side warming to 46°F overnight. Freezer (ZIR companion column installed alongside) holding -2°F normally. Issue developed gradually over a week.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Evaporator fan motor in the ZIC refrigerator column failed — year 8 unit, bearing wear. Classic split-temperature presentation: freezer fine (independent ZIR column has its own evap and fan), refrigerator side warming because the ZIC's evap fan stopped circulating cold air. Compressor measured within spec. Condenser coil clean (Hancock Park older home, pet-free, low dust load).</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Evap fan motor replaced with OEM Monogram part (pre-ordered 3 days from GE Appliances Louisville network on phone-identified symptoms). Returned and installed, verified normal fresh-food side cooldown to 38°F within 6 hours. Flush-cabinet hinge alignment verified after the reinstall.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $385 total. Two-visit timing on the 3-day part lead, 2 hours on-site total.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="repair-card">
        <h3>Monogram ZSC2202JSS Advantium speed oven, Bel Air</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Advantium would heat in microwave-only mode but not in speed-cook (halogen) mode. Owner noticed gradually — speed cook ran longer and produced no browning, eventually stopped browning entirely.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Halogen lamps measured open-circuit on testing — both upper halogens had burned out, lower halogen still functional but reduced output. Year 5 unit, within the year 3-6 typical halogen service interval. Magnetron tested clean (microwave function working). Door interlock switches verified functional.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Both upper halogen lamps replaced with OEM Monogram parts. Lower halogen replaced preventively at owner request given matched-wear cycle. Verified speed-cook mode browning on test cycle. Documented 3-4 year preventive halogen inspection cadence.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $445 total (three halogen lamps + diagnostic + labor). Same-day, 90 minutes on-site.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
